<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Physical Health Guide</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e0f7fa, #b2ebf2);
            /* Gradient background */
            min-height: 100vh;
            color: #333;
            position: relative;
            overflow-x: hidden;
        }

        /* Subtle background pattern */
        body::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            background: url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/light-paper-fibers.png');
            opacity: 0.1;
            z-index: -1;
        }

        header {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #00695c, #004d40);
            color: white;
            padding: 40px 20px;
            text-align: center;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }

        header h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
        }

        header p {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }

        .sections {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 40px;
            padding: 60px 20px;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        .card {
            background: white;
            padding: 25px;
            width: 280px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            text-align: center;
            box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
            transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
            cursor: pointer;
            overflow: hidden;
            position: relative;
        }

        .card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-10px);
            box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }

        .card::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 5px;
            background: #00796b;
            transition: height 0.3s;
        }

        .card:hover::before {
            height: 10px;
        }

        .card img {
            width: 100%;
            height: 160px;
            object-fit: cover;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .card h2 {
            color: #00796b;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .card p {
            color: #555;
            font-size: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.4;
        }

        a {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: inherit;
        }

        .list-page {
            padding: 40px 20px;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
            border-radius: 15px;
            margin: 0 20px 40px;
        }

        .list-page h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #004d40;
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
        }

        .pose {
            background: white;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 25px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            max-width: 900px;
            transition: transform 0.3s;
        }

        .pose:hover {
            transform: scale(1.02);
        }

        .pose h2 {
            color: #00796b;
            font-size: 1.7rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .pose p {
            color: #666;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .pose img {
            width: 100%;
            max-height: 320px;
            object-fit: contain;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin-top: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        }

        footer {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #00695c, #004d40);
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            position: relative;
            bottom: 0;
            width: 100%;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to Your Path to Wellness</h1>
        <p>Explore Yoga & Mudras for a Healthier Lifestyle</p>
    </header>

    <section class="sections">
        <a href="#yoga-section">
            <div class="card">
                <img src="styles/phyimg/yoga.jpg" alt="Yoga" />
                <h2>Yoga</h2>
                <p>Powerful Yoga Poses and their Benefits</p>
            </div>
        </a>
        <a href="#mudras-section">
            <div class="card">
                <img src="styles/phyimg/mudra.jpg" alt="Mudras" />
                <h2>Mudras</h2>
                <p>Essential Mudras and their Benefits</p>
            </div>
        </a>
    </section>

    <div class="list-page" id="yoga-section">
        <h1>Yoga Asanas & Their Benefits</h1>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>1. Tadasana (Mountain Pose)</h2>
            <p>Improves posture, balance, and calmness.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/tadasana.jpg" alt="Tadasana" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>2. Vrikshasana (Tree Pose)</h2>
            <p>Strengthens legs, improves focus and balance.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/vrikshasana.jpg"
                alt="Vrikshasana" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>3. Adho Mukha Svanasana (Downward Dog)</h2>
            <p>Stretches and strengthens the whole body.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/Adhomukha.jpg" alt="Downward Dog" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>4. Trikonasana (Triangle Pose)</h2>
            <p>Stretches legs, hips, spine; improves digestion.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/trikonasana.jpg"
                alt="Trikonasana" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>5. Bhujangasana (Cobra Pose)</h2>
            <p>Boosts spinal flexibility and opens the chest.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/Bhujangasana.jpg"
                alt="Bhujangasana" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>6. Paschimottanasana (Seated Forward Bend)</h2>
            <p>Improves digestion, calms the mind.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/pashimottasana.jpg"
                alt="Paschimottanasana" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>7. Ardha Matsyendrasana (Half Spinal Twist)</h2>
            <p>Increases spinal flexibility and detoxifies organs.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/half spin twist.jpg"
                alt="Ardha Matsyendrasana" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>8. Setu Bandhasana (Bridge Pose)</h2>
            <p>Strengthens the back and calms the brain.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/setuBanda.jpg"
                alt="Setu Bandhasana" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>9. Balasana (Child's Pose)</h2>
            <p>Relieves stress and fatigue, stretches hips and thighs.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/Balasana.jpg"
                alt="Balasana" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>10. Dhanurasana (Bow Pose)</h2>
            <p>Improves posture and strengthens the back.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/dhanurasana.jpg"
                alt="Dhanurasana" />
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="list-page" id="mudras-section">
        <h1>Mudras & Their Benefits</h1>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>1. Gyan Mudra</h2>
            <p>Enhances concentration and memory power.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/gyana.jpg" alt="Gyan Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>2. Prana Mudra</h2>
            <p>Boosts vitality and strengthens the immune system.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/prana.jpg"
                alt="Prana Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>3. Apana Mudra</h2>
            <p>Helps in detoxification and digestion.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/apana.jpg" alt="Apana Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>4. Vayu Mudra</h2>
            <p>Relieves joint pain and nervous disorders.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/vayu.jpg" alt="Vayu Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>5. Shunya Mudra</h2>
            <p>Alleviates ear pain and numbness.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/shunya.jpg" alt="Shunya Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>6. Surya Mudra</h2>
            <p>Reduces cholesterol, helps with weight loss.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/surya.jpg" alt="Surya Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>7. Varun Mudra</h2>
            <p>Improves skin texture and hydrates the body.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/varuna.jpg" alt="Varun Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>8. Apana Vayu Mudra</h2>
            <p>Good for heart health and emotional balance.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/apanavayu.jpg"
                alt="Apana Vayu Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>9. Linga Mudra</h2>
            <p>Generates heat and helps in respiratory issues.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/linga.jpg"
                alt="Linga Mudra" />
        </div>
        <div class="pose">
            <h2>10. Dhyana Mudra</h2>
            <p>Brings calmness and enhances meditation.</p><img src="styles/phyimg/dhyana.jpg" alt="Dhyana Mudra" />
        </div>
    </div>

    <footer>
        <p>©️ 2025 CareHub. All Rights Reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</body>

</html>